#### [BUG-3] Finance [getSummary](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/lib/api.ts#236-237) uses [(this.prisma as any).expense](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/lib/api.ts#175-176)

[finance.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/modules/finance/finance.service.ts#L64)

The `as any` cast bypasses type checking entirely. If the Expense model changes or is removed, this will silently fail at runtime with no compile-time warning.

**Fix:** Use `this.prisma.expense.findMany(...)` directly (Expense is in the Prisma schema). Remove the `as any` cast.

