#### [BUG-4] No error handling for invalid date strings in statistics API

[statistics.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/modules/statistics/statistics.service.ts)

[parseDateRange](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/modules/statistics/statistics.service.ts#169-177) calls `new Date(filters.startDate)` without validation. Invalid strings produce `Invalid Date`, causing silent query failures.

**Fix:** Add `isValid` check from date-fns before constructing the range.

