### ⚡ Performance Inefficiencies

---

#### [PERF-1] [getPatientBalance](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/lib/api.ts#237-238) fetches ALL payments into memory

[finance.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/modules/finance/finance.service.ts#L34-L43)

Fetches every payment for a patient, then filters in JS. For patients with hundreds of payments, this fetches all rows needlessly.

**Fix:** Use Prisma `aggregate` with conditional sum:
```typescript
const [paid, refunded] = await Promise.all([
    this.prisma.payment.aggregate({
        where: { clinicId, patientId, paymentType: 'PAYMENT' },
        _sum: { amount: true },
    }),
    this.prisma.payment.aggregate({
        where: { clinicId, patientId, paymentType: 'REFUND' },
        _sum: { amount: true },
    }),
]);
```

---

#### [PERF-2] [getSummary](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/lib/api.ts#236-237) fetches ALL payments & expenses into memory

[finance.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/modules/finance/finance.service.ts#L62-L72)

Same pattern: pulls every record then filters/reduces in JS. As transaction count grows, this becomes O(n) memory.

**Fix:** Use `groupBy` and `aggregate` queries to compute totals at the database level.

---

#### [PERF-3] Statistics [getOverview](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/modules/statistics/statistics.controller.ts#20-28) makes 8 parallel DB queries

[statistics.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/modules/statistics/statistics.service.ts#L21-L63)

8 separate `Promise.all` calls. Some can be combined (e.g., a single `groupBy` on [status](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/frontend/src/app/%28app%29/patients/%5Bid%5D/page.tsx#142-151) replaces 4 separate `count` queries).

**Fix:** Replace multiple `count` calls with a single `groupBy`:
```typescript
const statusCounts = await this.prisma.appointment.groupBy({
    by: ['status'], where, _count: { id: true },
});
```

---

#### [PERF-4] `PatientService.findOne` includes 20 appointments + 20 notes + all attachments

[patient.service.ts](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/klinikapp/backend/src/modules/patient/patient.service.ts#L56-L89)

This is a heavy query that fetches data for ALL tabs upfront even though the user typically views only one tab at a time.

**Fix:** Lazy-load tab data: fetch patient base info on initial load, then fetch appointments/notes/payments on tab switch via separate API calls.

